<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2716: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-11T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            11, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>47. Department has received reports of protests by Coalitionists in
                                Bluefields against alleged action of Government in preventing voters
                                from voting and to the effect that Coalitionists have cast their
                                votes in the presence of notaries. Endeavor to get full report from
                                Consul and transmit to Department.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>